rComments: By far my favourite proff out of all the Law proffs in Ottawa! soooooo many modules but worth it
Extremely slow at giving feedback. We received grades and feedback for the assignments handed in during the semester only after the term was over.
Un des meilleurs profs à la faculté de droit

Mostly asynchronous 40 min Youtube vids, optional assignements to check understanding. Lots of small assigned evals. Readings online, they are short, not hard. Flexible due dates. Did good with online transition, was awesome about accommodating for missed material, meeting to re-explain concepts. Very slow grader tho, tougher to get feedback.
I loved the man. He's nice, helpful, sexy, and always available to students. As a prof, he's a bit harsh at times, but it's always fair.

Yes, the man is a harsh grader but he's fair. He's genuine, listens to his students and really tries to improve himself. He isn't arrogant, he might be blunt but he has no problem apologizing, if you point it to him

Extremely nice man. Wonderful explainations. Despite this, students don't seem to meet his expectations.Once you have recieved a mark from him, there doesn't seem like there is much room to improve. Overly hard marker
